y 7, 2021. Additionally, contracts with different lengths are available for graduate and professional students through interim housing.  Residents with Fall 2020 one-semester contracts in SSR receive two weeks of the winter interim period in the cost of their contract at the end of their contract, but will still need to apply for the time they plan to stay on campus. Spring interim is not included with a spring one-semester contract.    Room Style  Room      1 Person Studio  $12,428    2 Person Apartment  $9,927    3 Person Apartment  $9,726    4 Person Apartment  $9,840    2 or 3 Person Efficiency Apartment  $8,469         Meal Plans     Meal plans are required for all halls except MRH, PSR, SSR, and TBH. Meal plans can be used in either of the two dining locations on campus - 605 Commons at Student Center East and JST Dining Center on South Campus  Flames Fare is accepted at Campus Retail Locations including: Chick-Fil-A, Panda Express, Halsted Street Station, Morgan Street Station, Au Bon Pain, Leaf & Bean Cafe, Daley Grind, Freshii, and the West Marketplace.  Students may use up to 4 entry swipes per day.  Meal plans reset each Monday.  Flames Fare amounts below are for the entire year, the amount is split between Fall and Spring semesters.  More can be added at any time at  dragoncenter.uic.edu.    2019-2020 Meal Plan Option Details  2019-2020 Academic Year Rates      Ember (15 Meals/week + $100 in Flames Fare)  $3,178    Ember Plus (15 Meals/week + $300 in Flames Fare)  $3,378    Ignite (10 Meals/week + $500 in Flames Fare)  $3,390    Ignite Plus (10 Meals/week + $700 in Flames Fare  $3,590    Blaze (19 Meals/week + $600 in Flames Fare)  $4,197    Blaze Plus (19 Meals/week + $800 in Flames Fare)  $4,397    Block (320 meals/academic year + $500 in Flames Fare)  $3,390          Housing Rates Ping                         UIC Logo        Campus Housing         Future    Apply    Housing Rates    Residence Halls    Services    Why Live on Campus      Current    App